RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 25 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT'S GIRL stalked the pace from three wide down the backstretch then was coaxed going into the final turn and took the lead at the quarter pole, pulled away and drew off in the stretch. WA WA WEE WA prompted the pace from the two path down the backstretch then made a move to engage the leader at the quarter pole but was no match for the winner and was clearly second best. CAYMAN QUEEN was unhurried to the final turn then made a rail bid and tipped out to three wide in upper stretch for a late rally. SHE'SMYSMOKESHOW rushed up from between horses to take a clear lead going into the first turn, held that position to the quarter pole where she was overtaken and tired. SODDY DAISY raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then made a three or four wide bid on the backstretch but lacked the late response. SCRAPBOOK saved ground and didn't make a serious bid. PIPPA'S PROSPECT raced near the back from off the rail but was not a threat. TRUE RED SLEW was off the pace from between horses to the three furlong marker and was done, eased, walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: True Red Slew
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, done, eased, walked off

ENTRY.NAME: Soddy Daisy
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, bid 3-4w, no late response

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight's Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, coaxed, led 1/4, drew off

UNLUCKY IN LOVE pressed the pace from between horses to the three furlong marker then dropped back and finished evenly. GOOD BY FAITH pressed the pace from three wide to the three furlong marker then retreated. STAND BY TIME trailed the field and was outrun.

BEAUDEAN raced off the pace from three wide to the quarter pole and dropped back. APRIORITY AVENGER raced in the middle of the pack while racing four wide down the backstretch and tired at the end of the bend.
